# Step-by-Step

Let's create a hook that manages a boolean toggle. This is a common pattern for modals, dropdowns, etc.

## 1. Start with the logic in a component

```jsx
function Component() {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
  const toggle = () => setIsOpen(prev => !prev);
  // ...
}
```

## 2. Extract to a function

```jsx
function useToggle(initialValue = false) {
  const [value, setValue] = useState(initialValue);
  const toggle = () => setValue(prev => !prev);
  return [value, toggle]; // like useState
}
```

## 3. Use it in components

```jsx
function Modal() {
  const [isOpen, toggleIsOpen] = useToggle(false);
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={toggleIsOpen}>Open</button>
      {isOpen && <div>Modal content</div>}
    </>
  );
}
```

